<br>
Thanks for the advice, but I have one already. And thank god it involves people who aren't deliberately ignorant. <br>
<br>
Think about this sentence and mull it for a few seconds. This is a very good example of bad grammar. Let us break it down.<br>
<br>
I) Thanks for the advice,<br>
##Small and simple words...hard to fuck up..##<br>
<br>
II) but I have one already.   &lt;----notice the Period denoting the end of a sentence.<br>
##The sentence as a whole works...but then...##<br>
<br>
III) And thank god it involves people who aren't deliberately ignorant.<br>
##Ok now look at this..major major fuck up.And starts the sentence.  Now Praxx I don't know about you but to most of us and is what is known as a &quot;conjunction&quot; it's meaning is, with; also; along with; as well as and it is used to connect words with identical grammatical functions, like 'When I'm not jacking off to gay porn i'm smoking crack AND sniffing glue.'.  So we see that even you are not perfect, which I'm sure offers up no surprises to anyone but yourself.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
If you criticize expect the favour to be returned. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=spooksmcgee>SpooksMcgee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 9:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grammatical lesson</span><hr size=1> &quot;Thanks for the advice, but I have one already.&quot;<br>
